.SH NAME
VTTCue \- VTTCue
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]VTTCue\f[R] interface of the WebVTT API represents a cue that
can be added to the text track associated with a particular video (or
other media).
.PP
A cue defines the text to display in a particular timeslice of a video
or audio track, along with display properties such as its size,
alignment, and position.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue()\f[R]
Returns a newly created \f[CR]VTTCue\f[R] object that covers the given
time range and has the given text.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]This interface also inherits properties from
\f[CI]TextTrackCue\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.region\f[R]
A \f[CR]VTTRegion\f[R] object describing the video\[cq]s sub\-region
that the cue will be drawn onto, or \f[CR]null\f[R] if none is assigned.
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.vertical\f[R]
An enum representing the cue writing direction.
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.snapToLines\f[R]
\f[CR]true\f[R] if the \f[CR]VTTCue.line\f[R] attribute indicates an
integer number of lines or \f[CR]false\f[R] if it represents a
percentage of the video size.
This is \f[CR]true\f[R] by default.
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.line\f[R]
Represents the line positioning of the cue.
This can be the string \f[CR]auto\f[R] or a number whose interpretation
depends on the value of \f[CR]VTTCue.snapToLines\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.lineAlign\f[R]
An enum representing the alignment of the \f[CR]VTTCue.line\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.position\f[R]
Represents the indentation of the cue within the line.
This can be the string \f[CR]auto\f[R], a number representing the
percentage of the \f[CR]VTTCue.region\f[R], or the video size if
\f[CR]VTTCue.region\f[R] is \f[CR]null\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.positionAlign\f[R]
An enum representing the alignment of the cue.
This is used to determine what the \f[CR]VTTCue.position\f[R] is
anchored to.
The default is \f[CR]auto\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.size\f[R]
Represents the size of the cue, as a percentage of the video size.
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.align\f[R]
An enum representing the alignment of all the lines of text within the
cue box.
.TP
\f[B]VTTCue.text\f[R]
A string representing the contents of the cue.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
.TP
\f[B]getCueAsHTML()\f[R]
Returns the cue text as a \f[CR]DocumentFragment\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLE
.SS HTML
The following example adds a new \f[CR]TextTrack\f[R] to the video, then
adds cues using the \f[CR]TextTrack.addCue()\f[R] method, with a
\f[CR]VTTCue\f[R] object as the value.
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]video\f[R]
  controls
  src=\[dq]https://interactive\-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/media/cc0\-videos/friday.mp4\[dq]></\f[B]video\f[R]>
